label: Cluster ID
definition: Clusters were the unit of randomization, and each consisted of 1 or more administrative villages. Two or more neighboring may have been combined to create 1 cluster as long as the cluster of villages had at least 8 eligible pregnant women and shared a border.
dataSet: WASH Benefits Kenya Cluster Randomized Trial

label: Randomization block
definition: Each randomization block was made up of 9 adjacent clusters that were pair-matched by geography. Each cluster within the randomization block was randomly allocated to one of 8 intervention arms, including 2 clusters randomly allocated to the active control arm.
dataSet: WASH Benefits Kenya Cluster Randomized Trial

label: LNS consumed count
definition: Number of lipid-based nutrient supplement (LNS) sachets consumed by the household per week. LNS sachets were provided to study children as well as to older, age-eligible siblings (6 to 24 months) living in study households to prevent potential sharing of LNS with older siblings. Assessed at enrollment (year 0, pre-intervention baseline), 1 year after intervention initiation (midline) and 2 years after intervention initiation (endline).
dataSet: WASH Benefits Kenya Cluster Randomized Trial

label: Persons <=18 years living in house count
definition: Total number of children under 18 years of age that lived in the household. Assessed at enrollment (year 0, pre-intervention baseline).
dataSet: WASH Benefits Kenya Cluster Randomized Trial

label: Severely stunted
definition: Whether the participant was severely stunted, defined as having a length- or height-for-age z-score of less than -3. Anthropometry was assessed 1 year after intervention initiation (midline) and 2 years after intervention initiation (endline).
dataSet: WASH Benefits Kenya Cluster Randomized Trial

label: Stunted
definition: Whether the participant was stunted, defined as having a length- or height-for-age z-score of less than -2. Anthropometry was assessed 1 year after intervention initiation (midline) and 2 years after intervention initiation (endline).
dataSet: WASH Benefits Kenya Cluster Randomized Trial

label: Wasted
definition: Whether the participant was wasted, defined as having a weight-for-length or -height z-score of less than -2. Anthropometry was assessed 1 year after intervention initiation (midline) and 2 years after intervention initiation (endline).
dataSet: WASH Benefits Kenya Cluster Randomized Trial

label: Underweight
definition: Whether the participant was underweight, defined as having a weight-for-age z-score of less than -2. Anthropometry was assessed 1 year after intervention initiation (midline) and 2 years after intervention initiation (endline).
dataSet: WASH Benefits Kenya Cluster Randomized Trial

label: Length- or height-for-age z-score, using median stature
definition: Length- or height-for-age z-score, using median stature. Values greater than 6 or less than -6 were flagged and set to missing.  Anthropometry was assessed 1 year after intervention initiation (midline) and 2 years after intervention initiation (endline).
dataSet: WASH Benefits Kenya Cluster Randomized Trial

label: Weight-for-length or -height z-score, using median weight and median length or height
definition: Weight-for-length or -height z-score, using median weight and median length or height. Values greater than 5 or less than -5 were flagged and set to missing.  Anthropometry was assessed 1 year after intervention initiation (midline) and 2 years after intervention initiation (endline).
dataSet: WASH Benefits Kenya Cluster Randomized Trial

label: BMI-for-age z-score, using median weight and median length or height
definition: BMI-for-age z-score, using median weight and median length or height. Values greater than 5 or less than -5 were flagged and set to missing.  Anthropometry was assessed 1 year after intervention initiation (midline) and 2 years after intervention initiation (endline).
dataSet: WASH Benefits Kenya Cluster Randomized Trial

label: Weight-for-age z-score, using median weight
definition: Weight-for-age z-score, using median weight. Values greater than 5 or less than -6 were flagged and set to missing.  Anthropometry was assessed 1 year after intervention initiation (midline) and 2 years after intervention initiation (endline).
dataSet: WASH Benefits Kenya Cluster Randomized Trial

label: Head circumference-for-age z-score, using median circumference
definition: Head circumference-for-age z-score, using median circumference. Values greater than 5 or less than -5 were flagged and set to missing.  Anthropometry was assessed 1 year after intervention initiation (midline) and 2 years after intervention initiation (endline).
dataSet: WASH Benefits Kenya Cluster Randomized Trial

label: Median stature
definition: Median of 3 stature measurements. Stature was measured as either recumbent length or height while standing. Anthropometry was assessed 1 year after intervention initiation (midline) and 2 years after intervention initiation (endline).
dataSet: WASH Benefits Kenya Cluster Randomized Trial

label: Median head circumference
definition: Median of 3 head circumference measurements. Anthropometry of target children was assessed 1 year after intervention initiation (midline) and 2 years after intervention initiation (endline).
dataSet: WASH Benefits Kenya Cluster Randomized Trial

label: Diarrhea case during the last 7 days, caregiver report
definition: Whether the participant was classified as a diarrhea case within the last 7 days. To meet this definition of a diarrhea case, the participant must have had 3+ loose or watery stools in 24 hours OR 1+ stool with blood using a 7-day recall. This variable was used in the primary analysis to improve power as there was no evidence for differential recall by arm. Caregiver reported symptoms were assessed at enrollment (year 0, pre-intervention baseline), 1 year after intervention initiation (midline), and 2 years after intervention initiation (endline).
dataSet: WASH Benefits Kenya Cluster Randomized Trial

label: Diarrhea case during the last 2 days, caregiver report
definition: Whether the participant was classified as a diarrhea case within the last 2 days. To meet this definition of a diarrhea case, the participant must have had 3+ loose or watery stools in 24 hours OR 1+ stool with blood using a 2-day recall. Caregiver reported symptoms were assessed at enrollment (year 0, pre-intervention baseline), 1 year after intervention initiation (midline), and 2 years after intervention initiation (endline).
dataSet: WASH Benefits Kenya Cluster Randomized Trial

label: Bruising during the last 7 days, caregiver report
definition: Whether the participant had bruising (a negative control outcome measured to detect potential differential bias in symptom reporting) within in the last 7 days. Caregiver reported symptoms were assessed 1 year after intervention initiation (midline) and 2 years after intervention initiation (endline).
dataSet: WASH Benefits Kenya Cluster Randomized Trial

label: Bruising during the last 2 days, caregiver report
definition: Whether the participant had bruising (a negative control outcome measured to detect potential differential bias in symptom reporting) within in the last 2 days. Caregiver reported symptoms were assessed 1 year after intervention initiation (midline) and 2 years after intervention initiation (endline).
dataSet: WASH Benefits Kenya Cluster Randomized Trial

label: Mother's age
definition: Age of the participant's mother. Assessed at enrollment (year 0, pre-intervention baseline).
dataSet: WASH Benefits Kenya Cluster Randomized Trial

label: Median mother's height
definition: Median height of the participant's mother, based on measurements taken 1 or 2 years after intervention initiation (midline or endline). Maternal height was measured in later visits and not at enrollment because it could have been influenced by pregnancy.
dataSet: WASH Benefits Kenya Cluster Randomized Trial

label: Target child or sibling/neighbor
definition: Target child participants were in utero at enrollment and were the primary study population (referred to as 'index children' in the manuscript). Older sibling or neighbor participants were less than 36m at the time of target child enrollment.
